definitions.definition: A former settlement in Anatolia , on the coast of the Aegean Sea; An Ancient Greek settlement on the west coast of Asia Minor inhabited by the Ionians , one of the four main Hellenic tribes.
A place in the United States .

subdefinitions.definition: A city , the county seat of Ionia County , Michigan .
